## 9. Coordinator API (control plane)

All weights/deltas travel as base64-encoded `.npz` in JSON bodies (model ≈ 17 KB — fine over HTTP; no object store needed).

| Method & path | Body / returns | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `POST /register` | `{silo_id, n_rows}` → `{token}` | silo enrollment |
| `GET /round/current` | → `{round, version, deadline_utc, hyperparams}` or `{idle}` | poll for work |
| `GET /model/{version}` | → `{version, weights_b64, arch}` | fetch global model |
| `POST /update` | `{silo_id, round, delta_b64, n_samples, train_loss, wall_time_s}` → `{accepted, staleness}` | submit local update |
| `POST /drift` | `{silo_id, psi, feature}` | drift signal |
| `GET /metrics/latest` | → JSON snapshot | dashboard/debug |
| `GET /healthz` | → 200 | compose healthcheck |

Coordinator is single-process; a background thread runs the round loop (§6.1). Persist registry + metrics on a named volume so restarts resume from the latest model version.

