## 10. Implementation Phases & Acceptance Criteria

> Each phase = one or more git commits + green `make test`. **Do not proceed on red.** Every phase must run in `mode: dev` on a laptop in < 15 minutes.

**Phase 0 — Scaffold.** Repo layout, compose file (redpanda + coordinator + 3 silos + dashboard stubs), config loader, Makefile, CI-style `make test`.
*Accept:* `docker compose up` → all containers healthy; `GET /healthz` 200; pytest green (config round-trip test).

**Phase 1 — Data pipeline.** Kaggle download instructions (manual step; script checks file hash), amplifier, non-IID partitioner, feature pipeline, Parquet lakehouse writer.
*Accept:* partitioner unit test — silo row counts match `size_shares` ±1%, per-silo `type` distributions match Dirichlet draw (chi-square sanity); feature pipeline produces 0 nulls/NaNs; window-function features validated against a hand-computed 20-row fixture.

**Phase 2 — Model + distributed trainer.** NumPy MLP with gradient check; Mode A and Mode B trainers.
*Accept:* (a) analytic gradient matches finite differences (rel. err < 1e-5); (b) Mode A gradient over a 4-partition 10k-row DataFrame equals the single-machine full-batch gradient (atol 1e-6); (c) Mode B on 100k dev rows reaches ROC-AUC within 0.02 of sklearn `LogisticRegression` on identical features (MLP should in fact beat it).

**Phase 3 — FL loop.** Coordinator API, client polling loop, FedAvg aggregation, model registry, metrics.sqlite.
*Accept:* integration test — 3 silos, 10 rounds, IID split: global AUC-PR strictly improves over round 1 and reaches ≥ 0.90 of the centralized baseline's AUC-PR (baseline computed by a script that trains on pooled data).

**Phase 4 — Heterogeneity + robustness.** FedProx term, semi-sync deadlines + staleness, attack injectors, QWRA + trimmed-mean.
*Accept:* under `label_flip: {frac: 0.5}` on 1 of 5 silos, QWRA's final AUC-PR exceeds vanilla FedAvg's by a measurable margin (assert ≥ +0.03 in the dev-mode integration test); cosine filter flags the poisoned silo in ≥ 70% of rounds.

**Phase 5 — Privacy.** Clipping + Gaussian noise, per-round analytic-Gaussian ε, composed budget, registry logging.
*Accept:* unit test of ε computation against hand-computed reference values; end-to-end DP run completes with utility drop < 0.10 AUC-PR at σ = 0.8 on dev data.

**Phase 6 — Streaming.** Replayer → Redpanda → Structured Streaming ingest → lakehouse append; PSI drift monitor; drift injector; drift-modulated rounds.
*Accept:* replay 200k events at 2000 ev/s; lakehouse row count matches published count (exactly-once via foreachBatch idempotent writes or documented at-least-once + dedup on event id); injected drift (amount distribution ×3 after step T) raises PSI alert within 2 streaming batches.

**Phase 7 — Experiment harness + evaluation.** Config-driven runner executing §11 scenarios; CSV outputs; plot scripts (AUC-PR vs rounds, robustness bars, scalability curve, drift timeline, privacy–utility frontier).
*Accept:* `make experiment E=E1` … `E=E6` each produce their CSV + PNG artifacts; a `RESULTS.md` table is auto-generated.

**Phase 8 — Dashboard + polish.** Streamlit views: round progress, per-silo contributions/flags, global metrics, drift alerts, ε gauges; README with quickstart; architecture diagram export.
*Accept:* dashboard renders live during a 10-round dev run; README quickstart reproduced from scratch (`git clone` → `make dev-up` → results) by a team member on a clean machine.

