## 11. Experimental Evaluation Plan (this is the "better than existing" proof)

**Baselines:** (a) **Centralized** — pooled data, same MLP (privacy-violating upper bound); (b) **Local-only** — each silo trains alone, report mean/worst silo (lower bound); (c) **Vanilla FedAvg**; (d) **FedSpark full** (FedProx + QWRA).

**Metrics:** AUC-ROC, **AUC-PR** (primary — fraud is 0.13% positive), recall @ FPR = 1%, rounds-to-target-AUC-PR, communication cost (bytes/round), round wall time, local-epoch throughput (rows/s).

| ID | Question | Setup | Expected headline |
|---|---|---|---|
| E1 | Does FL approach centralized utility? Mode A vs B? | 5 silos, IID and α=0.5, 30 rounds | FedSpark within ~5% of centralized AUC-PR; Mode B ≈ Mode A utility at far fewer Spark jobs |
| E2 | Non-IID robustness | α ∈ {0.1, 0.5, 100} × {FedAvg, +FedProx, +QWRA} | FedProx+QWRA degrades least at α=0.1 |
| E3 | Poisoning robustness | 0/20/40% silos label-flipped; model-poison γ=5 | vanilla FedAvg collapses; QWRA holds within a few points of clean run |
| E4 | Drift adaptation | streaming run, drift injected mid-way; frozen model vs continued FL | frozen model's AUC-PR decays; FedSpark recovers within a few rounds of the PSI alert |
| E5 | **Scalability (the Spark claim)** | silo dataset 0.2M → 6.3M → 25M rows; partitions 2→8; vs single-process pandas trainer | Spark client scales near-linearly; pandas client OOMs or exceeds time budget at 25M |
| E6 | Privacy–utility frontier | σ ∈ {0.5, 0.8, 1.2}, R=30, plot ε vs AUC-PR | readable trade-off curve; usable utility at single-digit-to-moderate ε |

Every plot lands in `docs/figures/`; `RESULTS.md` is regenerated by `experiments/plots.py`. Fix seeds; run dev-mode scenarios ≥ 3 seeds and report mean ± std where wall time allows.

